df$Date <- as.Date(df$ObservationDate, format = '%m/%d/%y')
df$ObservationDate <- NULL
df$Last.Update <- NULL

df_USA <-df %>% 
  filter(Country.Region=='US')

# aggregate states to nationwide view
df_USA <- dplyr::group_by(df_USA, Date) %>% summarise(Confirmed = sum(Confirmed),
                                                   Deaths = sum(Deaths),
                                                   Recovered = sum(Recovered))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
n <- nrow(df_USA)
print(paste0('Observations: ', n))
## [1] "Observations: 366"
# add a few more features
df_USA$Active <- df_USA$Confirmed - df_USA$Recovered - df_USA$Deaths 
df_USA$MortRate <- df_USA$Deaths / df_USA$Confirmed
df_USA$RecRate <- df_USA$Recovered / df_USA$Confirmed
df_USA$Rec_vs_Mort <- df_USA$Recovered / df_USA$Deaths

# # show data frame
# df_USA

# Active Cases plot
ggplot(df_USA,aes(Date,Active))+geom_point()+labs(title='Active Cases')

# Number of Deaths plot
ggplot(df_USA,aes(Date,Deaths))+geom_point()+labs(title='Deaths')

# Number of Recoveries plot
ggplot(df_USA,aes(Date,Recovered))+geom_point()+labs(title='Recoveries')

# Plot of mortality per day
ggplot(df_USA,aes(Date,MortRate))+geom_point()+labs(title='Mortality Rate')

ts_confirmed <- read_csv(file = "time_series_covid_19_confirmed.csv",
                         col_types = cols(
                           .default = col_double(),
                           `Province/State` = col_character(),
                           `Country/Region` = col_character()
                         ))

ts_recovered <- read_csv(file = "time_series_covid_19_recovered.csv",
                         col_types = cols(
                           .default = col_double(),
                           `Province/State` = col_character(),
                           `Country/Region` = col_character()
                         ))

ts_deaths <- read_csv(file = "time_series_covid_19_deaths.csv",
                      col_types = cols(
                        .default = col_double(),
                        `Province/State` = col_character(),
                        `Country/Region` = col_character()
                      ))
codes <- read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plotly/datasets/master/2014_world_gdp_with_codes.csv',
                  col_types = cols(
                    COUNTRY = col_character(),
                    `GDP (BILLIONS)` = col_double(),
                    CODE = col_character()
                  ))

ts_confirmed <- ts_confirmed %>%
  gather("Date", "Confirmed", -c("Province/State", "Country/Region", "Lat", "Long")) %>%
  mutate(Date = as.Date(Date, "%m/%d/%y")) 
View(ts_confirmed)

ts_recovered <- ts_recovered %>%
  gather("Date", "Recovered", -c("Province/State", "Country/Region", "Lat", "Long")) %>%
  mutate(Date = as.Date(Date, "%m/%d/%y"))

ts_deaths <- ts_deaths %>%
  gather("Date", "Deaths", -c("Province/State", "Country/Region", "Lat", "Long")) %>%
  mutate(Date = as.Date(Date, "%m/%d/%y"))
ts_total <- ts_confirmed %>%
  left_join(ts_deaths) %>%
  left_join(ts_recovered) %>%
  mutate(Recovered = replace_na(Recovered, replace = 0))
## Joining, by = c("Province/State", "Country/Region", "Lat", "Long", "Date")
## Joining, by = c("Province/State", "Country/Region", "Lat", "Long", "Date")
cases_latest <- ts_total %>%
  group_by(`Country/Region`, Date) %>%
  summarise(Confirmed  = sum(Confirmed),
            Recovered = sum(Recovered),
            Deaths = sum(Deaths)) %>%
  mutate("New Cases" = Confirmed - lag(Confirmed, 1) ) %>%
  filter(Date == max(Date))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'Country/Region' (override with `.groups` argument)
day_latest <- max(cases_latest$Date)
cases_total_date <- ts_total %>%
  rename(Region = `Country/Region`) %>%
  group_by(Date) %>%
  summarise(Confirmed = sum(Confirmed),
            Deaths = sum(Deaths),
            Recovered = sum(Recovered)) %>%
  mutate("New_Cases" = Confirmed - lag(Confirmed, 1))
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
cases_total_date$New_Cases[is.na(cases_total_date$New_Cases)] <- 0 

cases_total_latest <- cases_total_date %>%
  filter(Date == max(Date))
#creating code variable to match the country with country code
codes <- codes %>%
  select(COUNTRY, CODE) %>%
  rename(Region = COUNTRY ,
         Code = CODE) %>%
  rownames_to_column("id")

codes$id <- as.integer(codes$id)

#Top 10 countries with most confirmed cases
top_10_confirmed <- cases_latest %>%
  select('Country/Region', Confirmed) %>%
  arrange(desc(Confirmed))

top_10_confirmed[1:10,] %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(`Country/Region`,Confirmed), y = Confirmed )) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill  = "orange", width = 0.8) +geom_text(aes(label=Confirmed))+
